('w_economy_C1_12','externality','/ˌɛkstɜːrˈnælɪti/','noun','외부 효과','A side effect of an economic activity affecting others.','Pollution is a negative {externality}.','오염은 부정적 외부 효과예요.','externality','C1','economy',1,'externality pollution environment economy'),
('w_economy_C1_13','moral hazard','/ˈmɒrəl ˈhæzərd/','noun','도덕적 해이','Taking more risk because someone else bears the cost.','Bailouts can create {moral hazard}.','구제 금융은 도덕적 해이를 만들 수 있어요.','moral hazard','C1','economy',1,'moral hazard risk bank bailout'),
('w_economy_C1_14','asymmetric information','/ˌeɪsɪˈmɛtrɪk ˌɪnfəˈmeɪʃən/','noun','정보 비대칭','When one party has more information than the other.'{Asymmetric information} causes market inefficiency.','정보 비대칭은 시장 비효율성을 초래해요.','asymmetric information','C1','economy',1,'asymmetric information market party'),
('w_economy_C1_15','crowding out','/ˈkraʊdɪŋ aʊt/','noun','구축 효과','When government borrowing reduces private investment.','Heavy public spending can cause {crowding out}.','과도한 공공 지출은 구축 효과를 일으킬 수 있어요.','crowding out','C1','economy',1,'crowding out government private investment'),
('w_economy_C1_16','multiplier effect','/ˈmʌltɪplaɪər ɪˈfɛkt/','noun','승수 효과','When an initial economic change leads to a larger final change.','Government spending creates a {multiplier effect}.','정부 지출은 승수 효과를 만들어요.','multiplier effect','C1','economy',1,'multiplier effect spending ripple economy'),
('w_economy_C1_17','structural unemployment','/ˈstrʌktʃərəl ˌʌnɪmˈplɔɪmənt/','noun','구조적 실업','Unemployment caused by changes in the economy''s structure.'{Structural unemployment} requires retraining programs.','구조적 실업은 재훈련 프로그램이 필요해요.','structural unemployment','C1','economy',1,'structural unemployment industry change worker'),
('w_economy_C1_18','cyclical unemployment','/ˈsɪklɪkəl ˌʌnɪmˈplɔɪmənt/','noun','경기적 실업','Unemployment caused by economic downturns.'{Cyclical unemployment} rises during recessions.','경기적 실업은 경기 침체 중에 증가해요.','cyclical unemployment','C1','economy',1,'cyclical unemployment recession layoff'),
('w_economy_C1_19','purchasing power','/ˈpɜːrtʃɪsɪŋ ˈpaʊər/','noun','구매력','The value of money in terms of what it can buy.','Inflation reduces {purchasing power}.','인플레이션은 구매력을 감소시켜요.','purchasing power','C1','economy',1,'purchasing power money value inflation'),
('w_economy_C1_20','balance of payments','/ˈbæləns əv ˈpeɪmənts/','noun','국제 수지','A record of all financial transactions between a country and others.','The {balance of payments} showed a surplus.','국제 수지가 흑자를 보였어요.','balance of payments','C1','economy',1,'balance of payments trade current account'),
('w_economy_C1_21','current account','/ˈkɜːrənt əˈkaʊnt/','noun','경상 수지','The record of a country''s trade in goods and services.','The {current account} deficit widened.','경상 수지 적자가 확대됐어요.','current account','C1','economy',1,'current account trade flow international'),
('w_economy_C1_22','sovereign debt','/ˈsɒvrɪn dɛt/','noun','국가 채무','Money owed by a national government.'{Sovereign debt} levels are rising across Europe.','유럽 전역에서 국가 채무 수준이 오르고 있어요.','sovereign debt','C1','economy',1,'sovereign debt government bond eurozone'),
('w_economy_C1_23','fiscal stimulus','/ˈfɪskəl ˈstɪmjʊləs/','noun','재정 부양책','Government spending to boost the economy.','The government launched a large {fiscal stimulus}.','정부가 대규모 재정 부양책을 시작했어요.','fiscal stimulus','C1','economy',1,'fiscal stimulus spending recovery economy'),
('w_economy_C1_24','structural reform','/ˈstrʌktʃərəl rɪˈfɔːrm/','noun','구조 개혁','Changes to the fundamental way the economy works.'{Structural reforms} improved long-term productivity.','구조 개혁이 장기 생산성을 향상시켰어요.','structural reform','C1','economy',1,'structural reform policy change economy'),
('w_economy_C1_25','income inequality','/ˈɪnkʌm ˌɪnɪˈkwɒlɪti/','noun','소득 불평등','The unequal distribution of income across a population.'{Income inequality} has grown in many countries.','많은 나라에서 소득 불평등이 심화됐어요.','income inequality','C1','economy',1,'income inequality gap wealth distribution'),
('w_economy_C1_26','Gini coefficient','/ˈdʒiːni ˌkoʊɪˈfɪʃənt/','noun','지니 계수','A measure of income inequality ranging from 0 to 1.','The country has a high {Gini coefficient}.','그 나라는 지니 계수가 높아요.','Gini coefficient','C1','economy',1,'Gini coefficient inequality measure chart'),
('w_economy_C1_27','supply-side economics','/səˈplaɪ saɪd ˌiːkəˈnɒmɪks/','noun','공급 중시 경제학','Economic theory focusing on production incentives.'{Supply-side economics} advocates for lower taxes on business.','공급 중시 경제학은 기업 세금 감면을 옹호해요.','supply-side economics','C1','economy',1,'supply side economics tax cut production'),
('w_economy_C1_28','demand-side economics','/dɪˈmɑːnd saɪd ˌiːkəˈnɒmɪks/','noun','수요 중시 경제학','Economic theory focusing on boosting consumer demand.'{Demand-side economics} supports government spending during downturns.','수요 중시 경제학은 경기 침체 시 정부 지출을 지지해요.','demand-side economics','C1','economy',1,'demand side economics stimulus consumer'),
('w_economy_C1_29','helicopter money','/ˈhɛlɪkɒptər ˈmʌni/','noun','헬리콥터 머니','Direct cash payments from the central bank to citizens.','Some economists proposed {helicopter money} to boost demand.','일부 경제학자들은 수요 증대를 위해 헬리콥터 머니를 제안했어요.','helicopter money','C1','economy',1,'helicopter money cash stimulus central bank'),
('w_economy_C1_30','yield curve','/jiːld kɜːrv/','noun','수익률 곡선','A chart showing interest rates across different bond maturities.','An inverted {yield curve} often signals recession.','역전된 수익률 곡선은 종종 경기 침체를 예고해요.','yield curve','C1','economy',1,'yield curve inversion bonds chart'),
('w_economy_C1_31','forward guidance','/ˈfɔːrwərd ˈɡaɪdəns/','noun','포워드 가이던스','Central bank communication about future policy intentions.','The Fed used {forward guidance} to calm markets.','연준이 시장을 안정시키기 위해 포워드 가이던스를 활용했어요.','forward guidance','C1','economy',1,'forward guidance central bank communication'),
('w_economy_C1_32','productivity','/ˌprɒdʌkˈtɪvɪti/','noun','생산성','The efficiency with which output is produced.','Technology improved worker {productivity}.','기술이 노동자 생산성을 향상시켰어요.','productivity','C1','economy',1,'productivity worker output efficiency'),
('w_economy_C1_33','price ceiling','/praɪs ˈsiːlɪŋ/','noun','가격 상한','A maximum legal price for a product.','The government imposed a {price ceiling} on fuel.','정부가 연료에 가격 상한을 부과했어요.','price ceiling','C1','economy',1,'price ceiling regulation maximum government'),
('w_economy_C1_34','price floor','/praɪs flɔːr/','noun','가격 하한','A minimum legal price for a product.','The minimum wage is a type of {price floor}.','최저 임금은 가격 하한의 일종이에요.','price floor','C1','economy',1,'price floor minimum wage regulation'),
('w_economy_C1_35','capital flight','/ˈkæpɪtl flaɪt/','noun','자본 도피','Large-scale movement of assets out of a country.'{Capital flight} followed the currency crisis.','통화 위기 이후 자본 도피가 발생했어요.','capital flight','C1','economy',1,'capital flight outflow crisis currency'),

