('w_economy_C2_01','econometrics','/ɪˌkɒnəˈmɛtrɪks/','noun','계량 경제학','The use of statistical methods to analyse economic data.'{Econometrics} is used to test economic hypotheses empirically.','계량 경제학은 경제 가설을 실증적으로 검증하는 데 사용돼요.','econometrics','C2','economy',1,'econometrics statistics data regression'),
('w_economy_C2_02','fiduciary','/fɪˈdjuːʃiəri/','adjective','신탁의','Relating to a duty to act in another party''s best interest.','The fund manager has a {fiduciary} duty to investors.','펀드 매니저는 투자자에 대한 신탁 의무가 있어요.','fiduciary','C2','economy',1,'fiduciary duty trust fund legal'),
('w_economy_C2_03','securitization','/sɪˌkjʊərɪtaɪˈzeɪʃən/','noun','증권화','Pooling financial assets and selling them as securities.'{Securitization} of mortgages spread risk across the system.','모기지의 증권화가 시스템 전반에 위험을 확산시켰어요.','securitization','C2','economy',1,'securitization mortgage bonds financial'),
('w_economy_C2_04','collateralized','/kəˈlætərəlaɪzd/','adjective','담보화된','Backed by collateral as security for a debt.'{Collateralized} debt obligations were at the centre of the crisis.','담보화된 채무 증권이 위기의 중심에 있었어요.','collateralized','C2','economy',1,'collateralized CDO mortgage debt'),
('w_economy_C2_05','monopsony','/məˈnɒpsəni/','noun','수요 독점','A market with only one buyer and many sellers.','A labour market {monopsony} suppresses wages.','노동 시장의 수요 독점은 임금을 억제해요.','monopsony','C2','economy',1,'monopsony buyer market power wage'),
('w_economy_C2_06','rent-seeking','/rɛnt siːkɪŋ/','noun','지대 추구','Gaining wealth by manipulating the economic environment.'{Rent-seeking} behaviour reduces overall social welfare.','지대 추구 행동은 전반적인 사회 복지를 감소시켜요.','rent-seeking','C2','economy',1,'rent-seeking lobbying regulatory capture'),
('w_economy_C2_07','Keynesian','/ˈkeɪnziən/','adjective','케인스주의의','Based on the economic theories of John Maynard Keynes.'{Keynesian} economics supports fiscal stimulus in downturns.','케인스주의 경제학은 경기 침체 시 재정 부양을 지지해요.','Keynesian','C2','economy',1,'Keynesian economics government spending policy'),
('w_economy_C2_08','neoliberal','/ˌniːoʊˈlɪbərəl/','adjective','신자유주의적','Favouring free markets, deregulation, and reduced government.'{Neoliberal} policies dominated the 1980s and 1990s.','신자유주의 정책이 1980~90년대를 지배했어요.','neoliberal','C2','economy',1,'neoliberal free market policy reform'),
('w_economy_C2_09','heterodox','/ˈhɛtərədɒks/','adjective','비정통의','Departing from mainstream or accepted economic theories.'{Heterodox} economists challenge conventional growth models.','비정통 경제학자들은 기존의 성장 모델에 이의를 제기해요.','heterodox','C2','economy',1,'heterodox economics alternative theory'),
('w_economy_C2_10','exogenous','/ɛkˈsɒdʒɪnəs/','adjective','외생적인','Originating from outside the economic model.','An oil shock is an {exogenous} variable.','유가 충격은 외생 변수예요.','exogenous','C2','economy',1,'exogenous variable shock external model'),
('w_economy_C2_11','endogenous','/ɛnˈdɒdʒɪnəs/','adjective','내생적인','Originating from within the economic model.','Technological progress is treated as {endogenous} in new growth theory.','기술 진보는 신성장 이론에서 내생적으로 처리돼요.','endogenous','C2','economy',1,'endogenous growth model internal variable'),
('w_economy_C2_12','Pareto efficiency','/pəˈreɪtoʊ ɪˈfɪʃənsi/','noun','파레토 효율','An allocation where no one can be made better off without making someone worse off.'{Pareto efficiency} is the standard benchmark in welfare economics.','파레토 효율은 후생 경제학의 표준 기준이에요.','Pareto efficiency','C2','economy',1,'Pareto efficiency welfare economics optimum'),
('w_economy_C2_13','Nash equilibrium','/næʃ ˌiːkwɪˈlɪbriəm/','noun','내쉬 균형','A stable state in game theory where no player wants to change strategy.','The {Nash equilibrium} predicts the outcome of strategic interactions.','내쉬 균형은 전략적 상호작용의 결과를 예측해요.','Nash equilibrium','C2','economy',1,'Nash equilibrium game theory strategy'),
('w_economy_C2_14','deadweight loss','/ˈdɛdweɪt lɒs/','noun','경제적 손실','The loss of economic efficiency from market distortions.','A tax creates a {deadweight loss} in the market.','세금은 시장에서 경제적 손실을 발생시켜요.','deadweight loss','C2','economy',1,'deadweight loss tax efficiency triangle'),
('w_economy_C2_15','Dutch disease','/dʌtʃ dɪˈziːz/','noun','네덜란드병','When a natural resource boom harms other sectors of the economy.','The oil boom triggered {Dutch disease}.','석유 붐이 네덜란드병을 유발했어요.','Dutch disease','C2','economy',1,'Dutch disease oil boom exchange rate'),
('w_economy_C2_16','contagion','/kənˈteɪdʒən/','noun','금융 전염','The spread of economic crisis from one country to another.','Financial {contagion} spread from Asia to Latin America.','금융 전염이 아시아에서 남미로 퍼졌어요.','contagion','C2','economy',1,'contagion crisis spread global financial'),
('w_economy_C2_17','regulatory capture','/ˈrɛɡjʊlətɔːri ˈkæptʃər/','noun','규제 포획','When regulators serve the interests of the industries they oversee.'{Regulatory capture} undermines effective market oversight.','규제 포획은 효과적인 시장 감독을 약화시켜요.','regulatory capture','C2','economy',1,'regulatory capture government industry lobby'),
('w_economy_C2_18','liquidity trap','/lɪˈkwɪdɪti træp/','noun','유동성 함정','When monetary policy becomes ineffective at zero interest rates.'{Liquidity trap} conditions existed in Japan for decades.','일본에서 수십 년간 유동성 함정 상태가 지속됐어요.','liquidity trap','C2','economy',1,'liquidity trap zero interest rate Japan'),
('w_economy_C2_19','balance sheet recession','/ˈbæləns ʃiːt rɪˈsɛʃən/','noun','대차대조표 불황','When widespread private debt repayment reduces aggregate demand.'{Balance sheet recessions} require fiscal rather than monetary remedies.','대차대조표 불황은 통화 정책보다 재정 정책이 필요해요.','balance sheet recession','C2','economy',1,'balance sheet recession debt deleveraging'),
('w_economy_C2_20','twin deficit','/twɪn ˈdɛfɪsɪt/','noun','쌍둥이 적자','Simultaneous fiscal deficit and current account deficit.','The country suffered from a persistent {twin deficit}.','그 나라는 지속적인 쌍둥이 적자로 어려움을 겪었어요.','twin deficit','C2','economy',1,'twin deficit fiscal current account'),
('w_economy_C2_21','financialization','/fɪˌnænʃəlaɪˈzeɪʃən/','noun','금융화','The growing role of financial motives in the economy.'{Financialization} has increased income inequality in advanced economies.','금융화는 선진국에서 소득 불평등을 심화시켰어요.','financialization','C2','economy',1,'financialization finance sector GDP'),
('w_economy_C2_22','creative destruction','/kriˈeɪtɪv dɪˈstrʌkʃən/','noun','창조적 파괴','The process by which new innovations replace old industries.'{Creative destruction} is central to Schumpeter''s economic theory.','창조적 파괴는 슘페터 경제 이론의 핵심이에요.','creative destruction','C2','economy',1,'creative destruction innovation disruption'),
('w_economy_C2_23','opportunity cost','/ˌɒpəˈtjuːnɪti kɒst/','noun','기회 비용','The value of the best alternative foregone when making a choice.','Every investment has an {opportunity cost}.','모든 투자에는 기회 비용이 있어요.','opportunity cost','C2','economy',1,'opportunity cost choice decision foregone'),
('w_economy_C2_24','comparative advantage','/kəmˈpærətɪv ˈædvɑːntɪdʒ/','noun','비교 우위','The ability to produce goods at a lower opportunity cost than others.'{Comparative advantage} explains the basis for international trade.','비교 우위는 국제 무역의 기반을 설명해요.','comparative advantage','C2','economy',1,'comparative advantage trade specialization'),
('w_economy_C2_25','market failure','/ˈmɑːrkɪt ˈfeɪljər/','noun','시장 실패','When the free market fails to allocate resources efficiently.'{Market failure} justifies government intervention.','시장 실패는 정부 개입을 정당화해요.','market failure','C2','economy',1,'market failure pollution public good'),
('w_economy_C2_26','information asymmetry','/ˌɪnfəˈmeɪʃən eɪˈsɪmɪtri/','noun','정보 비대칭','Unequal distribution of information between parties in a transaction.'{Information asymmetry} leads to adverse selection.','정보 비대칭은 역선택을 초래해요.','information asymmetry','C2','economy',1,'information asymmetry market lemon problem'),
('w_economy_C2_27','currency peg','/ˈkɜːrənsi pɛɡ/','noun','환율 고정','A policy of fixing a currency''s value to another currency.','The {currency peg} came under speculative attack.','환율 고정이 투기 공격을 받았어요.','currency peg','C2','economy',1,'currency peg fixed rate exchange'),
('w_economy_C2_28','repo rate','/ˈriːpoʊ reɪt/','noun','환매 조건부 채권 금리','The rate at which the central bank lends to commercial banks.','The central bank raised the {repo rate} to curb inflation.','중앙은행이 인플레이션을 억제하기 위해 RP금리를 올렸어요.','repo rate','C2','economy',1,'repo rate central bank lending monetary'),
('w_economy_C2_29','systemic risk','/sɪˈstɛmɪk rɪsk/','noun','시스템 위험','The risk that the failure of one part will collapse the whole system.'{Systemic risk} was underestimated before the 2008 crisis.','2008년 위기 이전에 시스템 위험이 과소평가됐어요.','systemic risk','C2','economy',1,'systemic risk financial crisis contagion'),
('w_economy_C2_30','speculative bubble','/ˈspɛkjʊlətɪv ˈbʌbəl/','noun','투기적 거품','When asset prices rise far above their fundamental value.','The dot-com {speculative bubble} burst in 2001.','닷컴 투기 거품이 2001년에 붕괴됐어요.','speculative bubble','C2','economy',1,'speculative bubble burst chart overvalued'),
('w_economy_C2_31','helicopter drop','/ˈhɛlɪkɒptər drɒp/','noun','헬리콥터 드롭','Unconventional monetary policy involving direct cash distribution.','Friedman''s {helicopter drop} metaphor describes printing money freely.','프리드먼의 헬리콥터 드롭 비유는 자유로운 화폐 발행을 설명해요.','helicopter drop','C2','economy',1,'helicopter drop money printing QE'),
('w_economy_C2_32','aggregate demand','/ˈæɡrɪɡɪt dɪˈmɑːnd/','noun','총수요','The total demand for goods and services in an economy.','Government spending boosts {aggregate demand}.','정부 지출은 총수요를 증가시켜요.','aggregate demand','C2','economy',1,'aggregate demand macroeconomics GDP curve'),
('w_economy_C2_33','aggregate supply','/ˈæɡrɪɡɪt səˈplaɪ/','noun','총공급','The total supply of goods and services in an economy.','A supply shock reduces {aggregate supply}.','공급 충격은 총공급을 줄여요.','aggregate supply','C2','economy',1,'aggregate supply curve production economy'),
('w_economy_C2_34','factor of production','/ˈfæktər əv prəˈdʌkʃən/','noun','생산 요소','Resources used to produce goods: land, labour, capital, enterprise.','Land is a classic {factor of production}.','토지는 전통적인 생산 요소예요.','factor of production','C2','economy',1,'factor of production land labour capital'),
('w_economy_C2_35','Tobin tax','/ˈtoʊbɪn tæks/','noun','토빈세','A tax on financial transactions to curb speculation.','Proponents argue the {Tobin tax} reduces market volatility.','지지자들은 토빈세가 시장 변동성을 줄인다고 주장해요.','Tobin tax','C2','economy',1,'Tobin tax financial transaction levy');


